events.name: Washington Wizards at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal made his first shot to give Washington a lead it never gave up.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma, Wizards beat Knicks 116-105 in Beal's return

headlines.description: — Trae Young's latest matchup against Luka Doncic was his first with Dejounte Murray.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, Hawks beat Doncic, Mavs 130-122 for 4th straight win

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored 26 points and the Charlotte Hornets held off the reeling Houston Rockets 122-117 to snap a five-game skid Wednesday night after LaMelo Ball injured his left ankle again.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball injured again as Hornets get 122-117 win over Rockets

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 25 points, Ja Morant had 24 and the Memphis Grizzlies won their 11th straight game to match the franchise record, beating the Cleveland Cavaliers 115-114 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies top Cavs, tie team record with 11th win in a row

events.name: Miami Heat at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo scored 26 points and the Miami Heat led comfortably from the first quarter on in a 124-98 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bam Adebayo scores 26 points, Heat beat Pelicans 124-98

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander and Isaiah Joe each scored 23 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder rolled past the Indiana Pacers 126-106 on Wednesday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder beat Pacers 126-106 for 4th straight victory

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen had 34 points and 12 rebounds to help the Utah Jazz beat the short-handed Los Angeles Clippers 126-103 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lauri Markkanen returns to help Jazz rout Clippers

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray hit a go-ahead floater with 55.9 seconds remaining, Nikola Jokic broke Denver’s record for assists on the way to his 14th triple-double of the season, and the Nuggets rallied for a 122-118 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Jokic help Nuggets rally past Timberwolves 122-118

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Sacramento coach Mike Brown has been lauding his team's depth all season. On Wednesday night the Kings showed it with one of their top players sidelined.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings beat Lakers 116-111 for 5th straight victory
